  "title": "Carpenter",
  "description": "<ul><li><strong>Structural Framing:</strong> Building, erecting, and repairing building frameworks, including walls, floors, partitions, rafters, and roof trusses.</li><li><strong>Finished Carpentry:</strong> Installing, installing doors, window frames, molding, trim, drywall, insulation, and kitchen cabinets.</li><li><strong>Measurement and Planning:</strong> Interpreting blueprints and technical drawings to calculate materials needed and ensure compliance with building codes and safety regulations.</li><li><strong>Material Prep:</strong> Cutting, shaping, and smoothing lumber, drywall, and other materials using hand and power tools.</li><li><strong>Site Preparation:</strong> Measuring, leveling, and prepping construction sites or renovation areas.</li><li><strong>Collaboration:</strong> Working with contractors, electricians, and plumbers to coordinate, install, and fix fixtures. </li></ul>",
